comments.body:
@MattPennerVVUSD Can you try if running `$result = $var | Select -First 10` is fast on an Azure AD joined PC?
I suspect it's because `$var | Select -First 10` will send the results through formatting system, which will try retrieving the values for the properties to be displayed. For some properties, the attempt to retrieve value somehow results in a network IO for the Azure AD joined machine.

@joeyaiello @theJasonHelmick This is an issue with the `ActiveDirectory` module. Where shall we transfer this to?

Thanks for confirming the behavior -- it's indeed as what I suspected.
You cannot disable the formatting system, also when you attempt to access any of those problematic properties of the returned AD object, you will experience the same problem.
@SteveL-MSFT This is an issue with the `ActiveDirectory` module. do you know where we should transfer this issue to?
